text.__SUMMARY__: Shorea uliginosa is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family. It is a tree found in Sumatra, Peninsular Malaysia and Borneo.
text.Sources: Ashton, P. (1998). "Shorea uliginosa". The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. IUCN. 1998: e.T33140A9762164. doi:10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T33140A9762164.en. Retrieved 22 December 2017.
